ratings.rComments: He is an awesome teacher. Lets just say lectures aren't a burden. He is absolutely hilarious and his class is really fun. Expect about 2 hours of homework a week, not too bad. Definitely would take his class again. He's awesome. As long as you do the work, you'll do well.

Lol is entertaing, but he doesn't actually teach much. Hw can get difficult. And tests too. They are all graded electronically so it is really strict. Others have talked about extra cedit, but I haven't seen any yet.
Alex is very personable and  a good time! He has great energy and class was so much fun! My best class of U of I!

Hilarious! take ACE 161 with him. He makes this class so fun and easy, and he takes his dog with him sometimes (you can also follow his Instagram.) do the projects and practice and you will be fine. attendance is required, some extra credit, windows computer and the latest office required. you will find the knowledge useful through your life
Good class. The material covered is very useful. Only downside is having to use a windows computer in order to complete assignments.

This guy is hilarious, curses like a sailor and has fun with his students. Very helpful material everything is graded online by a computer program. Only complaint is that you can't use a Mac - it must be on windows or else it won't be graded correctly.  Take this class for an easy A he will have you dying laughing the whole time with his stories.
Most helpful class of college!  I wish my current students had to take such a comprehensive computer course to complete assignments with ppt and word.
Great teacher, really funny. He sends revision email before every exam and very helpful. You won't regret taking his class!

Great teacher. He kept everything clear, concise, and to the point. He also made it easy to go to class. He was hilarious, and he always kept things interesting. I highly recommend doing the extra credit.

Alex is very straightforward with the information you need to know. The class is very easy with only three exams, three projects, and no final. Also, the extra credit assignments each week are quick and the only homework besides projects. I didn't even have to go in for the third exam because of all of the extra credit. Take this class!

Alex Lo is amazing! Do the extra credit. It's easy and helps you  a lot in the course. He is a very good professor and he is hilarious. I enjoyed going to his class every week.  He is always willing to help and the taxtbook may be expensive but it is mandatory if u plan in doing the extra credit.
Do the extra credit. You would be stupid not to do it.

Whassup, great class! a real teacher the real deal, why cant other  profs be good teachers like he is?  I had  fun and I actually learned something.  Alex is a genuine person, nothing like those dirty birkenstock wearing hippies the rest of them are, take his class you'll be glad you did.
Favorite Class. Love him!
WOOT WOOT
This is the class to take player, you can actually learn something, Alex is da Man!  I laughed so hard I almost broke my desk!  Why isnt he  teaching  more classes?

Alex is fantastic. He's hilarious, sarcastic, and will always keep you awake and entertained in class. Sometimes the tangents are the best part of class. In this case, a 2-hour class will pass by quickly.
The funniest guy I have ever met. I actually looked forward to class. I was laughing constantly in his class. Take ACE 161 with him not Rogalla. Easy A just do the extra credit!

My name is Franklin and I had Alex last year, he is the most awesome teacher ever!  If only he taught more subjects my life would be perfect, he's smart and funny.   It was the highlight of my day to go to his class.  Other professors could learn something from him about how to teach

I cant believe the negative comments form 2 years ago, it must have been someone who had lost their mind.  This is what I hoped college would be a funny smart and helpful professor, it makes learning fun and  I wish Alex would teach all my classes he is able to take  difficult concepts and make them understandable. His class rocks!!!--Rafferty
Best class ever. Hilarious and super easy. Do whatever you can to take it with Lo and not Rogalla. I laughed nonstop in this class, and I looked forward to it every week.

Alex is really funny and pretty sarcastic.  He makes class really easy and is genuinely interested in the success of his students.  As long as you go to class and do the extra credit opportunities (which are the only h/w assignments) you'll be golden.
I'm a kid who hates class and I enjoyed and looked forward to this class. Lo is awesome and hilarious and his class is easy. All I did was attend class and do homework and projects and got an easy A.
I always look forward to this class as to you never know what Lo's going to do.
I loved attending class. It was a great way to wake up in the morning at 8 am. This class was hilarious and very open. It was my favorite class of the semester.

easy class! TAKE IT! he's hilarious. the extra credit assignments are easy, and those are the only hw's you get. there are 3 large projects (1 word, 1 excel, 1 access/powerpoint) but you get a****load of time to do them. TAKE IT WITH LO, he's HILARIOUS!

Definitely take this class with Lo. Easy class, but you have to go to get points. Class is not bad at all and he always keeps it entertaining. If you want to do the extra credit assignments you need the textbook. But other than that you will never need the book if you take notes in class.
FUNNIEST GUY I EVER MET!!! I don't even know how this guys a teacher. He doesn't sound or look like one. very helpful. Very easy class.
contrary to popular belief, he does not put the "lo" in "blow"
Alex is awesome! His class is not that hard, and is extremely useful. He is hillarious. Take it with him if you can. He is much better than Rogalla. Definitely take this class with him!

Alex is hilarious! Class is fun and very useful. It's like 2hrs. of stand up comedy every week. It counts for 3 credit/hrs. even though there's only 2hrs. of class! Assignments are not that hard. Great Class!
Wow he sucks! take 161 with someone else if possible.

avoid! avoid! avoid!  Apparently he used to be cool but now it just seems that he hates life, and tries to enforce dominance through his intense knowledge of MS Word.  Not worth the massive workload with Lo.  Also, he pretty much insults and ridicules everyone.

horrible... avoid if you can!

There are way too many assignments, and easy material was actually tough on his exams.  Avoid if possible, I heard Valerie was easier / better this semester.  Struggling to keep my B-!
This guy is a riot!
Alex is awesome. If you need hours or you have to take this class take him, his class is useful and easy.
easy easy class. but u love to be there because its basically a comedy show for 2 hrs. great guy. makes this time fly by. take it w/ him. u wont regret it, i promise.

Top Notch!
he is a hilarious teacher, but if you have him make sure to set your facebook profile to private....he likes to pull those up in class...awkward
Excellent

WOW what an awesome teacher!!!!!! He cracks soo many jokes even if it an 8 o'clock class i would recommend taking it! the class will wake you up.... A very EASY A if you know how to use a computer. TAKE ACE 161 with ALEX!

Awesome teacher!! Very cool, down to earth, funny as hell. Alex is amazing! I would definitely hang out with him out of class. He's got tattoos and loves to swear and make jokes. Oh, and ACE 161 is easy as hell, just show up and do the work and there's no way you won't get an A :)
